10/11/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkish police reported on Saturday (8 November) that an operation conducted last week netted 507 kilos of heroin, the country's biggest single drug catch ever. 
Agents had been watching a group of smugglers and their laboratory in the province of Rize for months before moving in. 
Local media reported the arrest of 13 suspects.
Also Saturday, Croatian customs officers say they found 21 kilos of heroin in a car entering the country from Montenegro. 
Two Bulgarians in the vehicle were arrested. 
(AFP - 08/11/03)
